Sentencas: Novel glass-based composite seals prepared by tape casting are evaluated as sealing materials in solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Development of novel glass-based composite seals for planar intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The leakage rates are measured at the inlet pressure of 1, 2 and 3 psi under different compressive stresses and temperatures respectively.
Titulo: Development of novel glass-based composite seals for planar intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results show that all of measured leakage rates are lower than 0.01 sccm cm(-1) and increase with higher inlet pressure and lower test temperatures.
Titulo: Development of novel glass-based composite seals for planar intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The leakage rates during thermal cycling are conducted under a compressive stress of 20 psi at 750 degrees C, which indicate excellent thermal cycle stability of the seals.
Titulo: Development of novel glass-based composite seals for planar intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Good compatibility between seals and the adjacent components provide well interface contact which could avoid the formation of leakage paths.
Titulo: Development of novel glass-based composite seals for planar intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: When the seal is applied for single cell testing, the open circuit voltage of 1.13 V and undetectable degradation clearly demonstrate the applicable performance of glass-based composite seal in solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Development of novel glass-based composite seals for planar intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
